### Class Features
All of the following are class features of the duellist prestige class.

#### Weapon and Armor Proficiency
The duellist is proficient with all simple and martial weapons. Duellists are proficient with light armor but not with shields.

#### Level 1: Precise Strike (Ex)
A duellist gains the ability to strike precisely with a light or one-handed piercing weapon, adding her duellist level to her damage roll.

When making a precise strike, a duellist cannot attack with a weapon in her other hand or use a shield. A duellist’s precise strike only works against living creatures with discernible anatomies. Any creature that is immune to critical hits is also immune to a precise strike, and any item or ability that protects a creature from critical hits also protects a creature from a precise strike.

#### Level 1: Enhanced Mobility
Starting at 1st level, when wearing light or no armor and not using a shield, a duellist gains an additional +4 bonus to AC against attacks of opportunity caused when she moves out of a threatened square.

#### Level 2: Improved Reaction 
At 2nd level, a duellist gains a +2 bonus on initiative checks. At 9th level, the bonus increases to +4.

#### Level 3: Combat Reflexes
At 3rd level, when using a light or one-handed piercing weapon. You may make a number of additional attacks of opportunity per round equal to your Dexterity bonus.

#### Level 4: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 5: Riptose  
Starting at 5th level, a duellist can make an attack of opportunity against any creature whose attack she successfully parries, so long as the creature she is attacking is within reach.

#### Level 6: Elaborate Defence
Every weapon you wield gains the **Defensive Property**
**Defensive Property**: When you make an attack with this weapon, you can forgo a portion (or all) of your attack bonus. For every point of attack bonus sacrificed, you gain a +1 bonus to AC until the start of your next turn.

#### Level 7: Deflect Arrows
At 7th level, a duellist gains the benefit of the [Deflect Arrows](https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/combat-feats/deflect-arrows-combat) feat when using a light or one-handed piercing weapon. The duellist does not need a free hand to use this feat.

#### Level 8: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 9: No Retreat 
At 9th level, enemies adjacent to the duellist that take a disengage action provoke an attack of opportunity from the duellist.

#### Level 10: Crippling Critical 
When you confirm a critical hit using a light or one-handed piercing weapon, you can apply one of the following penalties in addition to the damage dealt: reduce all of the target’s speeds by 10 feet (minimum 5 feet), 1d4 points of Strength or Dexterity damage, –4 penalty on all saving throws, –4 penalty to Armor Class, or 2d6 points of bleed damage. These penalties last for 1 minute, except for ability damage, which must be healed normally, and bleed damage, which continues until the target receives magic healing or a DC 15 Medicine skill check.


